#: ../../language/error_codes/E4165.md:1
msgid "E4165"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4165.md:3
msgid "Compiler diagnostic name: `missing_op_as_view`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4165.md:5
msgid "Missing `op_as_view` method for array pattern matching."
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4165.md:7
msgid ""
"Open array patterns such as `[head, ..tail]` need a value that can "
"provide a view for the `..` part of the pattern. `op_as_view` is the "
"compiler's internal name for the `_[_:_]` view operator; in source code "
"this operation is provided by annotating a compatible method with "
"`#alias(\"_[_:_]\")`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4165.md:12
msgid "Erroneous example"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4165.md:14
msgid ""
"The following example tries to use an open array pattern on an `Int`, "
"which does not provide `op_as_view`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4165.md:17
msgid ""
"///|\n"
"\n"
"///|\n"
"fn first_and_rest(value : Int) -> Int {\n"
"  match value {\n"
"    [head, .. _tail] => head\n"
"    _ => 0\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"///|\n"
"test {\n"
"  ignore(first_and_rest)\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4165.md:21
msgid "MoonBit will report an error."
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4165.md:23
msgid "Suggestion"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4165.md:25
msgid ""
"Use an array-like value that provides the view operation. When defining "
"that operation, annotate the method with `#alias(\"_[_:_]\")`, for "
"example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4165.md:28
msgid ""
"#alias(\"_[_:_]\")\n"
"fn Type::view(self : Type, start? : Int = 0, end? : Int) -> View {\n"
"  ...\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4165.md:35
msgid ""
"The fixed example uses `Array[Int]`, which already provides this "
"operation:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4165.md:37
msgid ""
"///|\n"
"\n"
"///|\n"
"fn first_or_zero(values : Array[Int]) -> Int {\n"
"  match values {\n"
"    [head, .. _tail] => head\n"
"    [] => 0\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"///|\n"
"test {\n"
"  inspect(first_or_zero([1, 2, 3]), content=\"1\")\n"
"  inspect(first_or_zero([]), content=\"0\")\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

